Hi Doc,

I speak with a lot of 8th and 9th grade girls who consider speech and debate as extracurricular activities. They are often considered very nerdy, dorky, and the last ones to be invited out. Often, I see a designation of being socially uncomfortable as being expected behavior of someone into speech/debate. I am not but I'm wondering what kinds of perspective you have on speech and debate as it is related to the social sciences.

We're also going to eat live insects this year.

Closing the Wisdom Gap in the Great Books Curriculum
